You are using:
	•	numbers
	•	letters

You should reserve a few patterns early.

Add:

reserved

0-9 are numeric tokens
a-z are base tokens

future tokens may use:
# for system tags
$ for system commands

Even if unused now, this avoids collisions later.

⸻

7. rejection behavior (important UX)

What if a syllable cannot be mapped?

Add:

unknown rule

if syllable cannot be mapped:
use closest phonetic spelling

if still unclear:
mark as unknown token

Example:

??? or unk

Better than silent failure.

⸻

8. repetition handling

Speech often repeats:

go go go
uh uh

Add:

repeat rule

repeated syllables are stored as repeated tokens

no collapse unless explicitly requested

Keeps artifact faithful.

