Your reason is sound:
	•	word gaps and syllable gaps are often similar
	•	real speech timing does not always contain clean word boundaries
	•	if you impose words too early, you inject guesswork

So the hyphen UI says:

here is the sound chain as Beast heard it

That is the right abstraction.

I would keep the rule simple:

live ui rule

Use - between adjacent detected syllables in the current utterance.

Example:

i-c-that-u-r

After a longer boundary, either:
	•	break line
